New York  Life Insurance Co., the
insurer with a portfolio of more than $170 billion, has hired
Gerald Smith, chief executive officer of Smith Graham & Co.
Investment Advisors, to its Board of Directors.  Smith, whose firm manages more than $5 billion in fixed
income and equity portfolio strategies, will join the board on
November 1, the company said today in a statement distributed by
Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
